  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Compassion hearts serving COVID-19 in sickle-child</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Compassion hearts is a call for community to step up, find little ways to help Sickle cell anemia children during COVID-19. The rapid spread of COVID-19 has meant the Sickle cell anemia children we support have been disconnected from us for over 32 days. These families are not equipped to deal with the pandemic. With all diseases, the Sickle cell anemia child is always most at risk. We need to provide information, essential items and support to ensure these families we support are safe.</narrative>
  </description>
